# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: NeitherPath
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "No second knock came."
    new "No second knock came."

    old "Sarah was left to herself. Finally she could be alone."
    new "Sarah was left to herself. Finally she could be alone."

    old "Sarah had arrived early for the council meeting, as she often did, preparing her final notes. She found the stress a good motivator."
    new "Sarah had arrived early for the council meeting, as she often did, preparing her final notes. She found the stress a good motivator."

    old "Slowly the room had filled with Varga, Barion, Carolyn and Kravel. Only Thomas had yet to arrive."
    new "Slowly the room had filled with Varga, Barion, Carolyn and Kravel. Only Thomas had yet to arrive."

    old "Thomas had set out earlier in the day with Marion and an entourage to go stag hunting in the royal forest."
    new "Thomas had set out earlier in the day with Marion and an entourage to go stag hunting in the royal forest."

    old "Everyone had understood that Marion's humiliation, though perhaps deserved, had injured the relations between the crown and the old houses."
    new "Everyone had understood that Marion's humiliation, though perhaps deserved, had injured the relations between the crown and the old houses."

    old "And so, Thomas had set out to both hunt game and mend fences, hoping that he could offer exclusive import rights on Normandian wine to Marion, to make him forget his hurt."
    new "And so, Thomas had set out to both hunt game and mend fences, hoping that he could offer exclusive import rights on Normandian wine to Marion, to make him forget his hurt."

    old "Though Thomas was late, few complained, after all it was the prerogative of kings to arrive when they wanted."
    new "Though Thomas was late, few complained, after all it was the prerogative of kings to arrive when they wanted."

    old "Deciding on efficieny, the other members of the council had agreed to proceed with handling small affairs."
    new "Deciding on efficieny, the other members of the council had agreed to proceed with handling small affairs."

    old "Sarah knew that Thomas was never one to care much for land reform petitions, even on the best of days."
    new "Sarah knew that Thomas was never one to care much for land reform petitions, even on the best of days."

    old "The council meeting would have passed uneventful, had it not been for the sudden interuption."
    new "The council meeting would have passed uneventful, had it not been for the sudden interuption."

    old "A loud banging on the door rang out through the room, disrupting the proceedings."
    new "A loud banging on the door rang out through the room, disrupting the proceedings."

    old "Everyone turned towards the door in surprise."
    new "Everyone turned towards the door in surprise."

    old "Meetings of the council were rarely interupted, and even when done so, the interruption would be soft and almost apologetic."
    new "Meetings of the council were rarely interupted, and even when done so, the interruption would be soft and almost apologetic."

    old "Suddenly, the door burst open and a small cadre of five soldiers marched into the council room."
    new "Suddenly, the door burst open and a small cadre of five soldiers marched into the council room."

    old "It was general Barion who rose first."
    new "It was general Barion who rose first."

    old "Princess Sarah Rose..."
    new "Princess Sarah Rose..."

    old "Sarah noticed something off about him. Her heart began to race. Something was wrong."
    new "Sarah noticed something off about him. Her heart began to race. Something was wrong."

    old "By order of the Rosanna Interim Committee, I place you under arrest on suspicion of treason."
    new "By order of the Rosanna Interim Committee, I place you under arrest on suspicion of treason."

    old "These soldiers will take you back to your room until further order."
    new "These soldiers will take you back to your room until further order."

    old "Sarah felt her throat close up."
    new "Sarah felt her throat close up."

    old "They were trying to overthrow her family."
    new "They were trying to overthrow her family."

    old "Her own fear had only just set in, when she began to fear even more deeply for her brother, Thomas."
    new "Her own fear had only just set in, when she began to fear even more deeply for her brother, Thomas."

    old "Where is Thomas?!"
    new "Where is Thomas?!"

    old "Sarah nearly screamed the words."
    new "Sarah nearly screamed the words."

    old "That's not your concern, my lady. Please, allow these men to escort you back to your room. I promise no harm will come to you."
    new "That's not your concern, my lady. Please, allow these men to escort you back to your room. I promise no harm will come to you."

    old "Varga lept to his feet, drawing his blade."
    new "Varga lept to his feet, drawing his blade."

    old "Whomever so much as moves to put a hand on her, prepare to lose it!"
    new "Whomever so much as moves to put a hand on her, prepare to lose it!"

    old "A chaos was spreading through the room, Sarah had lost all control. Herself, her brother...she stood to lose everything."
    new "A chaos was spreading through the room, Sarah had lost all control. Herself, her brother...she stood to lose everything."

    old "You want to try your luck at fighting off five of Rosanna's finest soldiers? Fine."
    new "You want to try your luck at fighting off five of Rosanna's finest soldiers? Fine."

    old "Soldiers! Seize the princess, and if this lowborn creature tries to stop you, do what you must."
    new "Soldiers! Seize the princess, and if this lowborn creature tries to stop you, do what you must."

    old "The soldiers, in unison, moved forward."
    new "The soldiers, in unison, moved forward."

    old "Varga raised his sword. Sarah could see he was more than willing to throw his life away for hers."
    new "Varga raised his sword. Sarah could see he was more than willing to throw his life away for hers."

    old "But it wasn't to be so."
    new "But it wasn't to be so."

    old "The soldier leading the unit moved up first and drove the tip of his blade through Barion's back."
    new "The soldier leading the unit moved up first and drove the tip of his blade through Barion's back."

    old "So stunned was the old general, that he did not even find the time to turn around. His face in shock."
    new "So stunned was the old general, that he did not even find the time to turn around. His face in shock."

    old "He tried to utter words, but the blood spewed forth from his mouth, drowning him and his words."
    new "He tried to utter words, but the blood spewed forth from his mouth, drowning him and his words."

    old "Barion stumbled, attempting to seize the table and chair, but wherever he reached, blood flowed from his chest down unto his arms and hands, causing him to slip."
    new "Barion stumbled, attempting to seize the table and chair, but wherever he reached, blood flowed from his chest down unto his arms and hands, causing him to slip."

    old "As she collapsed down unto the floor, it was the Spymaster Kravel who first approached him."
    new "As she collapsed down unto the floor, it was the Spymaster Kravel who first approached him."

    old "I'm sorry, old friend."
    new "I'm sorry, old friend."

    old "Sarah tried to make sense of everything that was happening, she watched as General Barion spent his last moments in life, confused."
    new "Sarah tried to make sense of everything that was happening, she watched as General Barion spent his last moments in life, confused."

    old "Your soldiers have been inconvenienced on their way here. These ones happen to be mine."
    new "Your soldiers have been inconvenienced on their way here. These ones happen to be mine."

    old "General Barion uttered his last words, but none could ever recall what they were. His arms fell to the ground, and his life left him."
    new "General Barion uttered his last words, but none could ever recall what they were. His arms fell to the ground, and his life left him."

    old "Spymaster Kravel turned to Sarah."
    new "Spymaster Kravel turned to Sarah."

    old "Princess Sarah, there is an uprising under way. Your enemies are making their move."
    new "Princess Sarah, there is an uprising under way. Your enemies are making their move."

    old "My...enemies?"
    new "My...enemies?"

    old "The old houses, under the leadership of Marion Achillea, have risen their banners against you."
    new "The old houses, under the leadership of Marion Achillea, have risen their banners against you."

    old "The five old houses, those that drew their lineage and power back all the way to Rosanna's founding, had betrayed her family."
    new "The five old houses, those that drew their lineage and power back all the way to Rosanna's founding, had betrayed her family."

    old "Sarah struggled to even make sense of this. Centuries of loyalty, tossed aside as if it never meant anything."
    new "Sarah struggled to even make sense of this. Centuries of loyalty, tossed aside as if it never meant anything."

    old "If this was true, then she had not just lost their support. She had also lost their connections, their wealth and their armies."
    new "If this was true, then she had not just lost their support. She had also lost their connections, their wealth and their armies."

    old "What was Barion's part in all this?"
    new "What was Barion's part in all this?"

    old "Barion has been loyal to your family and Rosanna for all this life, but he has always seen the value of the noble families and their guiding hand."
    new "Barion has been loyal to your family and Rosanna for all this life, but he has always seen the value of the noble families and their guiding hand."

    old "I fear that Marion has managed to seduce him, convincing him that betraying you and your family would be for the greater good of the nation."
    new "I fear that Marion has managed to seduce him, convincing him that betraying you and your family would be for the greater good of the nation."

    old "Foolishly, he believed Marion."
    new "Foolishly, he believed Marion."

    old "Sarah tried to process it. Never had she imagined that the kindly old family friend would betray her so casually."
    new "Sarah tried to process it. Never had she imagined that the kindly old family friend would betray her so casually."

    old "Snakes, a voice told her. Snakes and vipers everywhere in this country."
    new "Snakes, a voice told her. Snakes and vipers everywhere in this country."

    old "When did you first learn this?"
    new "When did you first learn this?"

    old "Only earlier this morning."
    new "Only earlier this morning."

    old "They had kept their plans well hidden, but Barion saw me as a friend, and he confided in me shortly before the meeting began."
    new "They had kept their plans well hidden, but Barion saw me as a friend, and he confided in me shortly before the meeting began."

    old "He told you about their plans to betray me and my family?"
    new "He told you about their plans to betray me and my family?"

    old "Yes. There was only so much time, I moved as quickly as I could to dispatch my own soldiers to intercept his, but..."
    new "Yes. There was only so much time, I moved as quickly as I could to dispatch my own soldiers to intercept his, but..."

    old "But what?"
    new "But what?"

    old "Kravel paused a moment."
    new "Kravel paused a moment."

    old "I also send out a unit of soldiers towards the hunting woods, but I fear they won't arrive in time."
    new "I also send out a unit of soldiers towards the hunting woods, but I fear they won't arrive in time."

    old "In time for what?"
    new "In time for what?"

    old "In time to prevent them from seizing king Thomas."
    new "In time to prevent them from seizing king Thomas."

    old "It felt to Sarah as if her heart stopped."
    new "It felt to Sarah as if her heart stopped."

    old "Thomas...what...what are they going to do?"
    new "Thomas...what...what are they going to do?"

    old "I only know what Barion told me, but from what I gathered it was Marion's plan to lure your brother out from the castle and capture him."
    new "I only know what Barion told me, but from what I gathered it was Marion's plan to lure your brother out from the castle and capture him."

    old "They believed that with you and your brother under arrest, they could take over the country with little bloodshed."
    new "They believed that with you and your brother under arrest, they could take over the country with little bloodshed."

    old "Sarah steeled her mind."
    new "Sarah steeled her mind."

    old "Be calm, she told herself. Her own life, her brother's life...everything depended on how she would act going forward."
    new "Be calm, she told herself. Her own life, her brother's life...everything depended on how she would act going forward."

    old "She could not afford to let the emotions or panic take hold of her."
    new "She could not afford to let the emotions or panic take hold of her."

    old "Composure. She reminded herself in the voice of her father."
    new "Composure. She reminded herself in the voice of her father."

    old "They have failed, at the very least to seize me."
    new "They have failed, at the very least to seize me."

    old "As soon as the soldiers return from the hunting woods, I want to know what happened to Thomas."
    new "As soon as the soldiers return from the hunting woods, I want to know what happened to Thomas."

    old "Of course, Princess Sarah."
    new "Of course, Princess Sarah."

    old "Sarah turned to Varga."
    new "Sarah turned to Varga."

    old "Varga, you will immediately take command of all of Rosanna's armed forces. There isn't a moment to waste."
    new "Varga, you will immediately take command of all of Rosanna's armed forces. There isn't a moment to waste."

    old "Go and gather the commanders, see which are still loyal and which we have lost. We need a complete account of our remaining forces."
    new "Go and gather the commanders, see which are still loyal and which we have lost. We need a complete account of our remaining forces."

    old "Varga bowed."
    new "Varga bowed."

    old "I'll go right away."
    new "I'll go right away."

    old "Varga bowed, turned, and began to walk away, a purpose to his stride."
    new "Varga bowed, turned, and began to walk away, a purpose to his stride."

    old "Sarah turned to Lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah turned to Lady Carolyn."

    old "Begin by taking account of all our remaining finances. See if they haven't looted those too."
    new "Begin by taking account of all our remaining finances. See if they haven't looted those too."

    old "Sarah paused, then continued."
    new "Sarah paused, then continued."

    old "Also, give me a list of all the assets of the old houses that are in the capital."
    new "Also, give me a list of all the assets of the old houses that are in the capital."

    old "Lady Carolyn bowed and took her leave in turn."
    new "Lady Carolyn bowed and took her leave in turn."

    old "Finally, Sarah turned to Kravel."
    new "Finally, Sarah turned to Kravel."

    old "You must tell me everything you know about this plot, every little detail that Barion entrusted you with."
    new "You must tell me everything you know about this plot, every little detail that Barion entrusted you with."

    old "I must get a hold on what is happening, and I must begin to take back control."
    new "I must get a hold on what is happening, and I must begin to take back control."

    old "Very well, princess Sarah."
    new "Very well, princess Sarah."

    old "The most important thing is getting Thomas back alive."
    new "The most important thing is getting Thomas back alive."

    old "Sitting down together, Kravel walked Sarah through everything he knew."
    new "Sitting down together, Kravel walked Sarah through everything he knew."

    old "By the end, Sarah understood what she was facing."
    new "By the end, Sarah understood what she was facing."

    old "The old houses, feeling mocked and belittled by her family's use of their resources in the war against the eastern tribes, had grown resentful."
    new "The old houses, feeling mocked and belittled by her family's use of their resources in the war against the eastern tribes, had grown resentful."

    old "It was this resentment that Marion had played into."
    new "It was this resentment that Marion had played into."

    old "As the most prominent head of the most influential noble house in Rosanna, he had their ear and whispered his corruptions."
    new "As the most prominent head of the most influential noble house in Rosanna, he had their ear and whispered his corruptions."

    old "Sarah could not be certain, but she imagined that her refusal of his proposal had no doubt motivated part of his treason."
    new "Sarah could not be certain, but she imagined that her refusal of his proposal had no doubt motivated part of his treason."

    old "Perhaps I should have been kinder to him when I said no..."
    new "Perhaps I should have been kinder to him when I said no..."

    old "Perhaps, Princess, but don't hold it against yourself."
    new "Perhaps, Princess, but don't hold it against yourself."

    old "Many men propose, only to be told no. Very few of them go on to lead an insurrection because of it."
    new "Many men propose, only to be told no. Very few of them go on to lead an insurrection because of it."

    old "Whatever Marion is doing, I don't doubt that he must have been carrying these plans around for a long time."
    new "Whatever Marion is doing, I don't doubt that he must have been carrying these plans around for a long time."

    old "Your refusal is most likely just a simple excuse for him to do what was already in his heart."
    new "Your refusal is most likely just a simple excuse for him to do what was already in his heart."

    old "Sarah considered it. Perhaps, but she had little way of knowing what was in Marion's heart. She had always considered him loyal. How foolish, she now realized."
    new "Sarah considered it. Perhaps, but she had little way of knowing what was in Marion's heart. She had always considered him loyal. How foolish, she now realized."

    old "Perhaps you're right..."
    new "Perhaps you're right..."

    old "But it doesn't matter. What matters is putting a stop to this insurrection and getting Thomas back."
    new "But it doesn't matter. What matters is putting a stop to this insurrection and getting Thomas back."

    old "It was not long after that a messenger came to the council room, handing Kravel a letter."
    new "It was not long after that a messenger came to the council room, handing Kravel a letter."

    old "He opened it, studying its contents."
    new "He opened it, studying its contents."

    old "One of my men came back from the hunting woods."
    new "One of my men came back from the hunting woods."

    old "He informs us that they came across Marion's party and gave chase. They tried to pursue them, but his entourage escaped and managed to join up with an Achillea army unit."
    new "He informs us that they came across Marion's party and gave chase. They tried to pursue them, but his entourage escaped and managed to join up with an Achillea army unit."

    old "My men, they're only a small scouting party. They were no match for Marion's soldiers, and so they retreated."
    new "My men, they're only a small scouting party. They were no match for Marion's soldiers, and so they retreated."

    old "He paused."
    new "He paused."

    old "They have found no trace of Thomas..."
    new "They have found no trace of Thomas..."

    old "Sarah had to remind herself to be strong, but her heart wished she could cry out."
    new "Sarah had to remind herself to be strong, but her heart wished she could cry out."

    old "Is he dead?"
    new "Is he dead?"

    old "No sign means no body. Most likely, Marion and his men captured Thomas and brought him along. If that's the case, we must assume he's in their custody."
    new "No sign means no body. Most likely, Marion and his men captured Thomas and brought him along. If that's the case, we must assume he's in their custody."

    old "Sarah slammed her fist on the table."
    new "Sarah slammed her fist on the table."

    old "That fucking snake!"
    new "That fucking snake!"

    old "If I get my hands on Marion, he'll regret ever being born."
    new "If I get my hands on Marion, he'll regret ever being born."

    old "Kravel only nodded."
    new "Kravel only nodded."

    old "My lady, while I understand your anger in the moment, let me actually live up to my title as advisor."
    new "My lady, while I understand your anger in the moment, let me actually live up to my title as advisor."

    old "King Thomas is most likely their hostage."
    new "King Thomas is most likely their hostage."

    old "They will bring him to one of their forts, surrounded by soldiers loyal to their noble houses."
    new "They will bring him to one of their forts, surrounded by soldiers loyal to their noble houses."

    old "If we wish to have any chance of bringing him back alive, we will have to act with extreme caution."
    new "If we wish to have any chance of bringing him back alive, we will have to act with extreme caution."

    old "What's your point?"
    new "What's your point?"

    old "My point is that force and revenge alone won't be enough to guarantee your brother's safe return. When it comes to it, you might have to be willing to treat your enemies with mercy."
    new "My point is that force and revenge alone won't be enough to guarantee your brother's safe return. When it comes to it, you might have to be willing to treat your enemies with mercy."

    old "Sarah fell back into her chair."
    new "Sarah fell back into her chair."

    old "Perhaps..."
    new "Perhaps..."

    old "But let's catch this snake before we decide what to do with him."
    new "But let's catch this snake before we decide what to do with him."

